description: Starts migrating a bot from Amazon Lex V1 to Amazon Lex V2. Migrate your bot when you want to take advantage of the new features of Amazon Lex V2. For more information, see Migrating a bot in the Amazon Lex developer guide.

parameters.name: v1BotName
parameters.description: The name of the Amazon Lex V1 bot that you are migrating to Amazon Lex V2.

parameters.name: v1BotVersion
parameters.description: The version of the bot to migrate to Amazon Lex V2. You can migrate the $LATEST version as well as any numbered version.

parameters.name: v2BotName
parameters.description: The name of the Amazon Lex V2 bot that you are migrating the Amazon Lex V1 bot to. If the Amazon Lex V2 bot doesn't exist, you must use the CREATE_NEW migration strategy. If the Amazon Lex V2 bot exists, you must use the UPDATE_EXISTING migration strategy to change the contents of the Amazon Lex V2 bot.

parameters.name: v2BotRole
parameters.description: The IAM role that Amazon Lex uses to run the Amazon Lex V2 bot.

parameters.name: migrationStrategy
parameters.description: The strategy used to conduct the migration. CREATE_NEW - Creates a new Amazon Lex V2 bot and migrates the Amazon Lex V1 bot to the new bot. UPDATE_EXISTING - Overwrites the existing Amazon Lex V2 bot metadata and the locale being migrated. It doesn't change any other locales in the Amazon Lex V2 bot. If the locale doesn't exist, a new locale is created in the Amazon Lex V2 bot.

nested_items.name: v1BotName
nested_items.description: The name of the Amazon Lex V1 bot that you are migrating to Amazon Lex V2.

nested_items.name: v1BotVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the bot to migrate to Amazon Lex V2.

nested_items.name: v1BotLocale
nested_items.description: The locale used for the Amazon Lex V1 bot.

nested_items.name: v2BotId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for the Amazon Lex V2 bot.

nested_items.name: v2BotRole
nested_items.description: The IAM role that Amazon Lex uses to run the Amazon Lex V2 bot.

nested_items.name: migrationId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier that Amazon Lex assigned to the migration.

nested_items.name: migrationStrategy
nested_items.description: The strategy used to conduct the migration.

nested_items.name: migrationTimestamp
nested_items.description: The date and time that the migration started.
